Common Tricky Interview Questions for Developers
🔹 1. Logic / Puzzle-Based
🧩 Classic ones:
8 balls problem (you just did)
12 balls (one different, heavier/lighter unknown)
100 doors problem
Egg dropping problem
Water jug problem (measure 4L using 3L & 5L)

👉 Tests: logical thinking + optimization

🔹 2. Bit Manipulation Tricks
Find single non-duplicate element
Swap without temp (XOR)
Check if number is power of 2
Count set bits
Find missing number using XOR

👉 These are heavily used in problems on platforms like LeetCode

🔹 3. Array / Pattern Tricks
First missing positive
Move zeros to end
Two sum / three sum
Kadane’s Algorithm (max subarray)
Dutch National Flag problem (0s,1s,2s sort)

👉 Tests: pattern recognition

🔹 4. Sorting & Searching Edge Cases
Sort in O(n) (you asked this ✔️)
Find kth largest element
Binary search variations:
First/last occurrence
Peak element
Rotated sorted array search
🔹 5. String Tricks
Check anagram
Longest substring without repeating chars
Palindrome variations
String compression
🔹 6. Recursion & Backtracking
Generate subsets
Permutations
N-Queens
Maze problems

👉 Tests: thinking in trees

🔹 7. System / Design Thinking (VERY important for you)

Since you're moving into backend:

Design a URL shortener (like Bitly)
Design a cache system (like Redis)
Rate limiter design
API design for a service
